  <brief_title>Converting From Ropinirole Immediate Release (IR) To Ropinirole Controlled-Release for RLS (Restless Legs Syndrome)</brief_title>
  <official_title>A 4-Week, Randomized, Double-Blind, Cohort Study to Evaluate the Safety and Tolerability of Converting From Ropinirole Immediate Release (IR) to Ropinirole Extended Release (XR) Formulation in Patients With Restless Legs Syndrome (RLS)</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>GlaxoSmithKline</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>GlaxoSmithKline</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a multi-center, Phase III study to evaluate the safety and tolerability of proposed
      dose conversion recommendations for RLS subjects converting from ropinirole immediate
      release to ropinirole controlled-release for RLS.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
